---
/**
 * Savings showcase. Visualizes the before/after token cost on a
 * single recall: flat memory vs CTXone's budgeted recall for the
 * same topic.
 *
 * Calibrated to 5× on day one, with a line about how the ratio
 * climbs with graph size. The whole point of under-promising here
 * is that the user's actual experience (usually higher) becomes
 * an upside surprise, not a broken marketing claim.
 */
---

<section class="section savings">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="eyebrow">
			<span class="dot"></span>
			<span class="eyebrow-text">LIVE // ctx_savings_ratio</span>
		</div>
		<h2 class="section-title">5× on day one. More as your graph grows.</h2>
		<p class="section-lede">
			Every <code>recall</code> response includes a
			<code>_ctxone_stats</code> field showing exactly how many
			tokens you sent vs how many you would have sent if the
			model had seen the full memory graph. This isn't
			marketing — it's the live delta the Hub computes on
			every request.
		</p>

		<div class="compare">
			<div class="col col-flat">
				<div class="label">Flat memory</div>
				<div class="caption">What the model sees without CTXone</div>
				<div class="bar bar-flat">
					<span class="bar-inner"></span>
				</div>
				<div class="number number-flat">1,500 tokens</div>
				<div class="note">Every session, every time</div>
			</div>

			<div class="arrow">→</div>

			<div class="col col-ctx">
				<div class="label">CTXone recall</div>
				<div class="caption">What the model sees with CTXone</div>
				<div class="bar bar-ctx">
					<span class="bar-inner"></span>
				</div>
				<div class="number number-ctx">300 tokens</div>
				<div class="note">Topic-matched + pinned</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="ratio">
			<div class="ratio-box">
				<span class="x">5×</span>
				<span class="x-label">savings ratio (day one)</span>
			</div>
		</div>

		<p class="footnote">
			Shown: a fresh graph with a few dozen facts. As you write
			more, recall stays the same size but the baseline grows —
			the ratio climbs to <strong>10×, 20×, and higher</strong>
			on graphs that have been lived in for a week or more. Start
			at 5×, discover the rest.
			<a href="/how-it-works/token-savings/">See the math →</a>
		</p>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.savings {
		background:
			radial-gradient(
				ellipse 60% 50% at 50% 100%,
				rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.08),
				transparent 60%
			),
			var(--ctx-bg);
	}

	.eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.55rem;
		padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
		background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.08);
		border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.28);
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--ctx-success);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.eyebrow .dot {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: var(--ctx-success);
		box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.8);
		animation: blink 1.6s ease-in-out infinite;
	}

	@keyframes blink {
		0%, 100% {
			opacity: 1;
		}
		50% {
			opacity: 0.35;
		}
	}

	.eyebrow-text {
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.compare {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 2rem;
		margin: 2.5rem 0 2rem 0;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.col {
		flex: 1;
		min-width: 14rem;
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-lg);
		padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
		position: relative;
	}

	.col-flat {
		border-color: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.25);
	}

	.col-ctx {
		border-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.35);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.05);
	}

	.label {
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.col-flat .label {
		color: var(--ctx-error);
	}

	.col-ctx .label {
		color: var(--ctx-success);
	}

	.caption {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.bar {
		height: 1.1rem;
		background: #050505;
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border-lo);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-sm);
		overflow: hidden;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.bar-inner {
		display: block;
		height: 100%;
	}

	.bar-flat .bar-inner {
		width: 100%;
		background: repeating-linear-gradient(
			45deg,
			#ef4444,
			#ef4444 8px,
			#c0392b 8px,
			#c0392b 16px
		);
		box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.3);
	}

	/* 300/1500 = 20% — 5× savings */
	.bar-ctx .bar-inner {
		width: 20%;
		background: var(--ctx-success);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.6);
	}

	.number {
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
	}

	.number-ctx {
		color: var(--ctx-success);
		text-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.4);
	}

	.note {
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		margin-top: 0.25rem;
	}

	.arrow {
		font-size: 2rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	.ratio {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: flex-start;
		margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 0;
	}

	.ratio-box {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		padding: 1rem 1.75rem;
		background:
			radial-gradient(
				ellipse at center,
				rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.15),
				transparent 70%
			),
			var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.35);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-lg);
	}

	.x {
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 4.5rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: var(--ctx-success);
		line-height: 1;
		text-shadow:
			0 0 24px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.6),
			0 0 48px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.3);
	}

	.x-label {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.footnote {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		max-width: 40rem;
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	.footnote strong {
		color: var(--ctx-warn);
	}

	.footnote code,
	.section-lede code {
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-sm);
		font-size: 0.9em;
		color: var(--ctx-accent-text);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.compare {
			flex-direction: column;
		}
		.arrow {
			transform: rotate(90deg);
		}
		.x {
			font-size: 3.25rem;
		}
	}
</style>
